    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "It generally doesn't make much sense to mine as fast as possible, since if there aren't transactions, it will just create a huge empty blockchain. A better approach would be to mine only when there are transactions, and stop otherwise. There's a proposal from me that supports this, while also always striving towards lowering the difficulty (i.e. making blocks easy to mine when needed).\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/pull/3478",
