    "body": "> It generally doesn't make much sense to mine as fast as possible, since if there aren't transactions, it will just create a huge empty blockchain.\r\n\r\nIt depends :) In raiden (or similar projects) you may have block number dependent timeouts. In our (raiden) CI we make use of `geth`. While we can start the chain with a very low difficulty, we would like to be able to manipulate the block time (adjustment) for our tests in order to speed up CI.",
